  <thing id="c5CBloMagV" name="Blood Magic" description="When you reach 2nd level, you gain the ability to cast spells.\n\nCantrips. You know two cantrips: eldritch blast plus one of your choice from the warlock class list. You learn additional cantrips at higher levels as shown on the Blood Magic table. \nSpells Known of 1st-Level and Higher. You know two 1st-level warlock spells of your choice. \n\nThe Spells Known column of the Blood Magic table shows when you learn more warlock spells of 1st level or higher. The Spell Level column specifies the highest level spell you can learn in this way.\n\nWhenever you gain a level in this class, you can replace one warlock spell you know with another spell of a level that you can cast from the warlock spell list. \n\nHit Point Cost. Blood magic does not grant any spell slots. Instead, you cast your spells of 1st level or higher using your own life energy.\n\nCasting a spell of 1st level or higher costs 5 hit points per spell level. The Spell Level column of the Blood Magic table shows the highest level spell you can cast. Spellcasting Ability. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your warlock spells, since your spells are dark powers that you command through the sheer force of your presence. You use your Charisma whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability, and use your Charisma modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a\nwarlock spell you cast or making an attack roll with one. \n\nSpell save DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier \nSpell attack modifier = your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier \n\nSpellcasting Focus. You use fresh blood as a spellcasting focus. As long as you have drank fresh blood within the past 24 hours, you can cast spells without supplying the required material components, except for material components that list a gold piece cost.\n\nVampire Level | Cantrips Known | Spells Known | Spell Level\n2nd 2 2 1st\n3rd 2 3 1st\n4th 2 3 1st\n5th 2 4 2nd\n6th 2 4 2nd\n7th 2 5 2nd\n8th 2 5 2nd\n9th 2 6 3rd\n10th 3 6 3rd\n11th 3 7 3rd\n12th 3 7 3rd\n13th 3 8 4th\n14th 3 8 4th\n15th 3 9 4th\n16th 3 9 4th\n17th 4 10 5th\n18th 4 10 5th\n19th 4 11 5th\n20th 4 11 5th" compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="abAction" tag="None"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="c5CUnhSpeV" name="Unholy Spells" description="The spells on the Unholy Spells table count as warlock spells for you. You may learn them at the levels shown, but they count against your number of spells known." compset="ClSpecial">
    <tag group="abAction" tag="None"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="c5CBloLinV" name="Blood Link" description="Beginning at 6th level, when you drink a creature’s blood, it is more susceptible to your magic for 24 hours. During this time, any spell you cast on the creature which has a duration of longer than 1 round has its duration increased by 1 hour per spell level. If the spell requires concentration, you have advantage on saving throws you make to maintain concentration." compset="ClSpecial">
