  <thing id="c5CVamLair" name="Lair" description="You may establish a place as your lair by taking a long rest there for 6 consecutive days. The area of the lair may be no larger than a cube 500 feet per side, and can’t be the lair of another creature. The area ceases to be your lair if you don’t  take a long rest in it for 60 days, or if you establish a new lair. \n\nTurn Immunity. While in your lair, you are immune to effects that turn undead. \nLair Spells. While in your lair, you may innately cast the spells listed on the Lair Spells table, once you reach the level specified. Some spells may only be cast a limited number of times per day; you regain expended uses of those spells at sundown. \n\nWhen you use this ability to cast animate dead or create undead to reassert control over undead creatures that are in your lair, you don’t need to see the creatures or be within range, or even be\nwithin your lair; you can cast from anywhere.\n\nVampire\nLevel Lair Spells\n3rd alarm, animal friendship, arcane lock, darkness, fog cloud, speak with animals\n5th animate dead (1/day), nondetection\n7th blight\n9th animate dead (2/day), animate objects, hallow (1/day), insect plague\n11th circle of death, create undead (1/day), guards and wards (1/day)\n13th animate dead (3/day)\n15th control weather\n17th animate dead (4/day), storm of vengeance, weird\n19th create undead (2/day)" compset="ClSpecial"></thing>
